'''Margherita Joan (Miggy) Biller''' {{post-nominals|country=GBR|MBE}} is a British mathematics teacher, the head of mathematics at [[York College (York)|York College]]. She was named an MBE in the [[2016 New Year Honours]] "for services to mathematics in further education".<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/news/new-year-honours-full-list-of-yorkshire-s-recipients-1-7649687|title=New Year Honours: Full list of Yorkshire’s recipients|newspaper=[[Yorkshire Post]]|date=31 December 2015}}.</ref>
Biller taught mathematics at [[St Peter's School, York]] before moving to York College in 1988.<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.stpetersyork.org.uk/assets/0000/8415/79_405_-_OCT_1988.pdf|title=The Peterite|volume=405|date=1987–1988|page=5}}.</ref> At York College, she taught mathematics prodigy Daniel Lightwing, after whom the main character of the film ''[[X+Y]]'' was modeled.<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.artsyork.co.uk/xy-an-emotional-tale-about-a-mathematical-genius/|title=X+Y: An emotional tale about a maths genius|first=Danielle|last=Barge|date=17 March 2015|newspaper=Arts York}}.</ref> Her husband, [[Peter Biller]], is a historian at the [[University of York]].<ref>{{citation|url=http://homepage.ntlworld.com/david.cavalla/ian/roots.htm |title=Ian Heavens memorial |first=Miggy |last=Biller |accessdate=2015-12-31 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304105741/http://homepage.ntlworld.com/david.cavalla/ian/roots.htm |archivedate=2016-03-04 |df= }}.</ref>
